The paper deals with the capacity pre-log of a single-input multiple-output (SIMO) channel, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of Hironaka's theorem on resolution of singularities suggests a connection to algebraic geometry (cs.AG), but this is not the main focus of the paper. The paper also involves statistical inference (cs.SI) and signal processing (cs.NI), as well as system theory (cs.SY) and machine learning (cs.LG) in the context of communication systems.
